de.learnlib.algorithms.adt.adt

Interface ADTNode<S,I,O>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - (hypothesis) state type
    I - input alphabet type
    O - output alphabet type
    All Superinterfaces:
    net.automatalib.graphs.Graph<ADTNode<S,I,O>,ADTNode<S,I,O>>, net.automatalib.graphs.IndefiniteGraph<ADTNode<S,I,O>,ADTNode<S,I,O>>, net.automatalib.graphs.IndefiniteSimpleGraph<ADTNode<S,I,O>>, Iterable<ADTNode<S,I,O>>, net.automatalib.graphs.ads.RecursiveADSNode<S,I,O,ADTNode<S,I,O>>, net.automatalib.graphs.SimpleGraph<ADTNode<S,I,O>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ADTLeafNode, ADTResetNode, ADTSymbolNode

    public interface ADTNode<S,I,O>
extends net.automatalib.graphs.ads.RecursiveADSNode<S,I,O,ADTNode<S,I,O>>
    The ADT equivalent of ADSNode. In contrast to regular adaptive distinguishing sequences, an ADT node may also represent a reset node that semantically separates multiple ADSs.
    Author:
    frohme

    • Method Detail

      • sift

        ADTNode<S,I,O> sift(SymbolQueryOracle<I,O> oracle,
                    net.automatalib.words.Word<I> prefix)
             throws UnsupportedOperationException
        Utility method, that sifts a given word through this ADTNode. If this node is a
        • symbol node, the symbol is applied to the system under learning and the corresponding child node (based on the observed output) is returned. If no matching child node is found, a new leaf node is returned instead
        • reset node, the system under learning is reset and the provided prefix is reapplied to the system
        • leaf node, an exception is thrown
        Parameters:
        oracle - the oracle used to query the system under learning
        prefix - the prefix to be re-applied after encountering a reset node
        Returns:
        the corresponding child node
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - when invoked on a leaf node (see getNodeType().
